Philadelphia, PA&ndash; Philadelphia today saw the most votes cast in the city&rsquo;s history as measured by percentage and raw numbers. Oddly enough, only about 4,000 people actually showed up at polling places to cast votes.
&ldquo;It was remarkably efficient,&rdquo; said Philly Mayor Nutter (D). &ldquo;We managed to break voting records without forcing people to leave work early or find the polling places. This is a model for the country.&rdquo;
For the numbers, 127 percent of the eligible voters were represented in the final number, and nearly 1,800,000 votes cast.
